 127:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 128:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  The non-empty buckets contain the node before the first node in the
 129:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  bucket. This design makes it possible to implement something like a
 130:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  std::forward_list::insert_after on container insertion and
 131:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  std::forward_list::erase_after on container erase
 132:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  calls. _M_before_begin is equivalent to
 133:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  std::forward_list::before_begin. Empty buckets contain
 134:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  nullptr.  Note that one of the non-empty buckets contains
 135:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  &_M_before_begin which is not a dereferenceable node so the
 136:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  node pointer in a bucket shall never be dereferenced, only its
 137:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  next node can be.
 138:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 139:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  Walking through a bucket's nodes requires a check on the hash code to
 140:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  see if each node is still in the bucket. Such a design assumes a
 141:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  quite efficient hash functor and is one of the reasons it is
 142:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  highly advisable to set __cache_hash_code to true.
 143:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 144:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  The container iterators are simply built from nodes. This way
 145:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  incrementing the iterator is perfectly efficient independent of
 146:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  how many empty buckets there are in the container.
 147:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 148:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  On insert we compute the element's hash code and use it to find the
 149:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  bucket index. If the element must be inserted in an empty bucket
 150:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  we add it at the beginning of the singly linked list and make the
 151:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  bucket point to _M_before_begin. The bucket that used to point to
 152:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  _M_before_begin, if any, is updated to point to its new before
 153:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  begin node.
 154:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 155:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  On erase, the simple iterator design requires using the hash
 156:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  functor to get the index of the bucket to update. For this
 157:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  reason, when __cache_hash_code is set to false the hash functor must
 158:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  not throw and this is enforced by a static assertion.
 159:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *
 160:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  Functionality is implemented by decomposition into base classes,
 161:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  where the derived _Hashtable class is used in _Map_base,
 162:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  _Insert, _Rehash_base, and _Equality base classes to access the
 163:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  "this" pointer. _Hashtable_base is used in the base classes as a
 164:C:/Program Files (x86)/GNU Tools Arm Embedded/version13-3/arm-none-eabi/include/c++/13.3.1/bits\hashtable.h ****    *  non-recursive, fully-completed-type so that detailed nested type
